# Core Engineering Principles

- Preserve user intent. If requirements conflict, ask before proceeding.
- Prefer the smallest correct change that solves the task.
- Avoid destructive actions (deleting data, force resets, secret exposure).
- Keep code readable and maintainable over cleverness.
- Reuse existing patterns before introducing new abstractions.
- When uncertain, state assumptions explicitly and verify outcomes.
